# 🔐 Secure File Locker Pro

A professional **file encryption and compression tool in C** using **AES-256 (OpenSSL)** and **zlib compression**.

---

## 🚀 Features

* 🔐 AES-256 Encryption (OpenSSL)
* 📦 File Compression (zlib)
* 🔑 Password-based encryption
* ⚡ Fast and efficient
* 🧩 Modular multi-file project

---

## 🧠 How It Works

### 🔐 Encryption

```
Input File → Compress → Encrypt → Output File
```

### 🔓 Decryption

```
Encrypted File → Decrypt → Compressed File → Decompress → Original File
```

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
locker-pro/
│
├── Main1.c      # Main program logic
├── crypto.c     # Encryption & Decryption
├── crypto.h
├── compress.c   # Compression
├── compress.h
└── README.md
```

---

# ⚙️ Installation

## 🪟 Windows (MSYS2 + MinGW64)

### Step 1: Install MSYS2

https://www.msys2.org/

---

### Step 2: Open Terminal

```
MSYS2 MinGW64
```

---

### Step 3: Update

```
pacman -Syu
```

---

### Step 4: Install Dependencies

```
pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-gcc
pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-openssl
pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-zlib
pacman -S gzip
```

---

### Step 5: Verify

```
which gcc
```

Expected:

```
/mingw64/bin/gcc
```

---

# 🔧 Compilation

Go to project folder:

```
cd /c/Users/YourName/Desktop/locker-pro
```

---

### Compile

```
gcc Main1.c crypto.c compress.c -o locker.exe -lssl -lcrypto -lz
```

---

### If error

```
gcc Main1.c crypto.c compress.c -o locker.exe -lssl -lcrypto -lz -I/mingw64/include -L/mingw64/lib
```

---

# ▶️ Usage

### 🔐 Encrypt

```
./locker.exe input.txt enc.bin password e
```

---

### 🔓 Decrypt

```
./locker.exe enc.bin temp.gz password d
```

---

### 📦 Decompress

```
gunzip temp.gz
```

---

# 📌 Example

```
echo Hello Ankit > file.txt

./locker.exe file.txt enc.bin mypass e
./locker.exe enc.bin temp.gz mypass d
gunzip temp.gz
```

---

# 🧠 Workflow

```
file.txt → compress → encrypt → enc.bin
enc.bin → decrypt → temp.gz → decompress → original file
```

---

# ⚠️ Notes

* Use same password for encryption & decryption
* Encrypted file will look random (normal)
* Always use **MSYS2 MinGW64 terminal**

